9 /// \file ----
10 /// This pass adds instructions to enable whole quad mode (strict or non-strict) ----
11 /// for pixel shaders, and strict whole wavefront mode for all programs. ----
12 /// ----
13 /// The "strict" prefix indicates that inactive lanes do not take part in ----
14 /// control flow, specifically an inactive lane enabled by a strict WQM/WWM will ----
15 /// always be enabled irrespective of control flow decisions. Conversely in ----
16 /// non-strict WQM inactive lanes may control flow decisions. ----
17 /// ----
18 /// Whole quad mode is required for derivative computations, but it interferes ----
19 /// with shader side effects (stores and atomics). It ensures that WQM is ----
20 /// enabled when necessary, but disabled around stores and atomics. ----
21 /// ----
22 /// When necessary, this pass creates a function prolog ----
23 /// ----
24 /// S_MOV_B64 LiveMask, EXEC ----
25 /// S_WQM_B64 EXEC, EXEC ----
26 /// ----
27 /// to enter WQM at the top of the function and surrounds blocks of Exact ----
28 /// instructions by ----
29 /// ----
30 /// S_AND_SAVEEXEC_B64 Tmp, LiveMask ----
31 /// ... ----
32 /// S_MOV_B64 EXEC, Tmp ----
33 /// ----
34 /// We also compute when a sequence of instructions requires strict whole ----
35 /// wavefront mode (StrictWWM) and insert instructions to save and restore it: ----
36 /// ----
37 /// S_OR_SAVEEXEC_B64 Tmp, -1 ----
38 /// ... ----
39 /// S_MOV_B64 EXEC, Tmp ----
40 /// ----
41 /// When a sequence of instructions requires strict whole quad mode (StrictWQM) ----
42 /// we use a similar save and restore mechanism and force whole quad mode for ----
43 /// those instructions: ----
44 /// ----
45 /// S_MOV_B64 Tmp, EXEC ----
46 /// S_WQM_B64 EXEC, EXEC ----
47 /// ... ----
48 /// S_MOV_B64 EXEC, Tmp ----
49 /// ----
50 /// In order to avoid excessive switching during sequences of Exact ----
51 /// instructions, the pass first analyzes which instructions must be run in WQM ----
52 /// (aka which instructions produce values that lead to derivative ----
53 /// computations). ----
54 /// ----
55 /// Basic blocks are always exited in WQM as long as some successor needs WQM. ----
56 /// ----
57 /// There is room for improvement given better control flow analysis: ----
58 /// ----
59 /// (1) at the top level (outside of control flow statements, and as long as ----
60 /// kill hasn't been used), one SGPR can be saved by recovering WQM from ----
61 /// the LiveMask (this is implemented for the entry block). ----
62 /// ----
63 /// (2) when entire regions (e.g. if-else blocks or entire loops) only ----
64 /// consist of exact and don't-care instructions, the switch only has to ----
65 /// be done at the entry and exit points rather than potentially in each ----
66 /// block of the region. ----
67 /// ----
68 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

93 StateStrictWWM = 0x2, ----

107 static raw_ostream &operator<<(raw_ostream &OS, const PrintState &PS) { 0

109 static const std::pair Mapping[] = { ----
110 std::pair(StateWQM, "WQM"), std::pair(StateStrictWWM, "StrictWWM"), ----
111 std::pair(StateStrictWQM, "StrictWQM"), std::pair(StateExact, "Exact")}; ----
112 char State = PS.State; 0

114 if (State & M.first) { 0

117 ----
118 if (State) 0

124 } ----

293 void SIWholeQuadMode::markInstruction(MachineInstr &MI, char Flag, 0
294 std::vector &Worklist) { ----
295 InstrInfo &II = Instructions[&MI]; 0
296 ----
297 assert(!(Flag & StateExact) && Flag != 0); 0
298 ----
299 // Remove any disabled states from the flag. The user that required it gets ----
300 // an undefined value in the helper lanes. For example, this can happen if ----
301 // the result of an atomic is used by instruction that requires WQM, where ----
302 // ignoring the request for WQM is correct as per the relevant specs. ----
303 Flag &= ~II.Disabled; 0
304 ----
305 // Ignore if the flag is already encompassed by the existing needs, or we ----
306 // just disabled everything. ----
307 if ((II.Needs & Flag) == Flag) 0
308 return; 0
309 ----
310 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "markInstruction " << PrintState(Flag) << ": " << MI); 0
311 II.Needs |= Flag; 0
312 Worklist.push_back(&MI); 0
313 } ----

315 /// Mark all relevant definitions of register \p Reg in usage \p UseMI. ----
316 void SIWholeQuadMode::markDefs(const MachineInstr &UseMI, LiveRange &LR, 0
317 Register Reg, unsigned SubReg, char Flag, ----
318 std::vector &Worklist) { ----
319 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "markDefs " << PrintState(Flag) << ": " << UseMI); 0
320 ----
321 LiveQueryResult UseLRQ = LR.Query(LIS->getInstructionIndex(UseMI)); 0
322 const VNInfo *Value = UseLRQ.valueIn(); 0
323 if (!Value) 0
324 return; 0
325 ----
326 // Note: this code assumes that lane masks on AMDGPU completely ----
327 // cover registers. ----
328 const LaneBitmask UseLanes = ----
329 SubReg ? TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubReg) 0
330 : (Reg.isVirtual() ? MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg) 0
331 : LaneBitmask::getNone()); 0
332 ----
333 // Perform a depth-first iteration of the LiveRange graph marking defs. ----
334 // Stop processing of a given branch when all use lanes have been defined. ----
335 // The first definition stops processing for a physical register. ----
336 struct PhiEntry { ----
337 const VNInfo *Phi; ----
338 unsigned PredIdx; ----
339 LaneBitmask DefinedLanes; ----
340 ----
341 PhiEntry(const VNInfo *Phi, unsigned PredIdx, LaneBitmask DefinedLanes) 0
342 : Phi(Phi), PredIdx(PredIdx), DefinedLanes(DefinedLanes) {} 0
343 }; ----
344 using VisitKey = std::pair; ----
345 SmallVector PhiStack; 0
346 SmallSet Visited; 0
347 LaneBitmask DefinedLanes; 0
348 unsigned NextPredIdx = 0; // Only used for processing phi nodes 0
349 do { ----
350 const VNInfo *NextValue = nullptr; 0
351 const VisitKey Key(Value, DefinedLanes); 0
352 ----
353 if (Visited.insert(Key).second) { 0
354 // On first visit to a phi then start processing first predecessor ----
355 NextPredIdx = 0; 0
356 } ----
357 ----
358 if (Value->isPHIDef()) { 0
359 // Each predecessor node in the phi must be processed as a subgraph ----
360 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LIS->getMBBFromIndex(Value->def); 0
361 assert(MBB && "Phi-def has no defining MBB"); 0
362 ----
363 // Find next predecessor to process ----
364 unsigned Idx = NextPredIdx; 0
365 auto PI = MBB->pred_begin() + Idx; 0
366 auto PE = MBB->pred_end(); 0
367 for (; PI != PE && !NextValue; ++PI, ++Idx) { 0
368 if (const VNInfo *VN = LR.getVNInfoBefore(LIS->getMBBEndIdx(*PI))) { 0
369 if (!Visited.count(VisitKey(VN, DefinedLanes))) 0
370 NextValue = VN; 0
371 } ----
372 } ----
373 ----
374 // If there are more predecessors to process; add phi to stack ----
375 if (PI != PE) 0
376 PhiStack.emplace_back(Value, Idx, DefinedLanes); 0
377 } else { ----
378 MachineInstr *MI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(Value->def); 0
379 assert(MI && "Def has no defining instruction"); 0
380 ----
381 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
382 // Iterate over all operands to find relevant definitions ----
383 bool HasDef = false; 0
384 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->all_defs()) { 0
385 if (Op.getReg() != Reg) 0
386 continue; 0
387 ----
388 // Compute lanes defined and overlap with use ----
389 LaneBitmask OpLanes = ----
390 Op.isUndef() ? LaneBitmask::getAll() 0
391 : TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(Op.getSubReg()); 0
392 LaneBitmask Overlap = (UseLanes & OpLanes); 0
393 ----
394 // Record if this instruction defined any of use ----
395 HasDef |= Overlap.any(); 0
396 ----
397 // Mark any lanes defined ----
398 DefinedLanes |= OpLanes; 0
399 } ----
400 ----
401 // Check if all lanes of use have been defined ----
402 if ((DefinedLanes & UseLanes) != UseLanes) { 0
403 // Definition not complete; need to process input value ----
404 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LR.Query(LIS->getInstructionIndex(*MI)); 0
405 if (const VNInfo *VN = LRQ.valueIn()) { 0
406 if (!Visited.count(VisitKey(VN, DefinedLanes))) 0
407 NextValue = VN; 0
408 } ----
409 } ----
410 ----
411 // Only mark the instruction if it defines some part of the use ----
412 if (HasDef) 0
413 markInstruction(*MI, Flag, Worklist); 0
414 } else { ----
415 // For physical registers simply mark the defining instruction ----
416 markInstruction(*MI, Flag, Worklist); 0
417 } ----
418 } ----
419 ----
420 if (!NextValue && !PhiStack.empty()) { 0
421 // Reach end of chain; revert to processing last phi ----
422 PhiEntry &Entry = PhiStack.back(); 0
423 NextValue = Entry.Phi; 0
424 NextPredIdx = Entry.PredIdx; 0
425 DefinedLanes = Entry.DefinedLanes; 0
426 PhiStack.pop_back(); 0
427 } ----
428 ----
429 Value = NextValue; 0
430 } while (Value); 0
431 } 0
432 ----
433 void SIWholeQuadMode::markOperand(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
434 const MachineOperand &Op, char Flag, ----
435 std::vector &Worklist) { ----
436 assert(Op.isReg()); 0
437 Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
438 ----
439 // Ignore some hardware registers ----
440 switch (Reg) { 0
441 case AMDGPU::EXEC: 0
442 case AMDGPU::EXEC_LO: ----
443 return; 0
444 default: 0
445 break; 0
446 } ----
447 ----
448 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "markOperand " << PrintState(Flag) << ": " << Op 0
449 << " for " << MI); ----
450 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
451 LiveRange &LR = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
452 markDefs(MI, LR, Reg, Op.getSubReg(), Flag, Worklist); 0
453 } else { ----
454 // Handle physical registers that we need to track; this is mostly relevant ----
455 // for VCC, which can appear as the (implicit) input of a uniform branch, ----
456 // e.g. when a loop counter is stored in a VGPR. ----
457 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(Reg.asMCReg())) { 0
458 LiveRange &LR = LIS->getRegUnit(Unit); 0
459 const VNInfo *Value = LR.Query(LIS->getInstructionIndex(MI)).valueIn(); 0
460 if (!Value) 0
461 continue; 0
462 ----
463 markDefs(MI, LR, Unit, AMDGPU::NoSubRegister, Flag, Worklist); 0
464 } ----
465 } ----
466 } ----

468 /// Mark all instructions defining the uses in \p MI with \p Flag. ----
469 void SIWholeQuadMode::markInstructionUses(const MachineInstr &MI, char Flag, 0
470 std::vector &Worklist) { ----
471 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "markInstructionUses " << PrintState(Flag) << ": " 0
472 << MI); ----
473 ----
474 for (const MachineOperand &Use : MI.all_uses()) 0
475 markOperand(MI, Use, Flag, Worklist); 0
476 } 0

478 // Scan instructions to determine which ones require an Exact execmask and ----
479 // which ones seed WQM requirements. ----
480 char SIWholeQuadMode::scanInstructions(MachineFunction &MF, 0
481 std::vector &Worklist) { ----
482 char GlobalFlags = 0; 0
483 bool WQMOutputs = MF.getFunction().hasFnAttribute("amdgpu-ps-wqm-outputs"); 0
484 SmallVector SetInactiveInstrs; 0
485 SmallVector SoftWQMInstrs; 0
486 bool HasImplicitDerivatives = ----
487 MF.getFunction().getCallingConv() == CallingConv::AMDGPU_PS; 0
488 ----
489 // We need to visit the basic blocks in reverse post-order so that we visit ----
490 // defs before uses, in particular so that we don't accidentally mark an ----
491 // instruction as needing e.g. WQM before visiting it and realizing it needs ----
492 // WQM disabled. ----
493 ReversePostOrderTraversal RPOT(&MF); 0
494 for (MachineBasicBlock *MBB : RPOT) { 0
495 BlockInfo &BBI = Blocks[MBB]; 0
496 ----
497 for (MachineInstr &MI : *MBB) { 0
498 InstrInfo &III = Instructions[&MI]; 0
499 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
500 char Flags = 0; 0
501 ----
502 if (TII->isWQM(Opcode)) { 0
503 // If LOD is not supported WQM is not needed. ----
504 if (!ST->hasExtendedImageInsts()) 0
505 continue; 0
506 // Only generate implicit WQM if implicit derivatives are required. ----
507 // This avoids inserting unintended WQM if a shader type without ----
508 // implicit derivatives uses an image sampling instruction. ----
509 if (!HasImplicitDerivatives) 0
510 continue; 0
511 // Sampling instructions don't need to produce results for all pixels ----
512 // in a quad, they just require all inputs of a quad to have been ----
513 // computed for derivatives. ----
514 markInstructionUses(MI, StateWQM, Worklist); 0
515 GlobalFlags |= StateWQM; 0
516 continue; 0
517 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::WQM) { 0
518 // The WQM intrinsic requires its output to have all the helper lanes ----
519 // correct, so we need it to be in WQM. ----
520 Flags = StateWQM; 0
521 LowerToCopyInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
522 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::SOFT_WQM) { 0
523 LowerToCopyInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
524 SoftWQMInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
525 continue; 0
526 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::STRICT_WWM) { 0
527 // The STRICT_WWM intrinsic doesn't make the same guarantee, and plus ----
528 // it needs to be executed in WQM or Exact so that its copy doesn't ----
529 // clobber inactive lanes. ----
530 markInstructionUses(MI, StateStrictWWM, Worklist); 0
531 GlobalFlags |= StateStrictWWM; 0
532 LowerToMovInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
533 continue; 0
534 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::STRICT_WQM || 0
535 TII->isDualSourceBlendEXP(MI)) { 0
536 // STRICT_WQM is similar to STRICTWWM, but instead of enabling all ----
537 // threads of the wave like STRICTWWM, STRICT_WQM enables all threads in ----
538 // quads that have at least one active thread. ----
539 markInstructionUses(MI, StateStrictWQM, Worklist); 0
540 GlobalFlags |= StateStrictWQM; 0
541 ----
542 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::STRICT_WQM) { 0
543 LowerToMovInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
544 } else { ----
545 // Dual source blend export acts as implicit strict-wqm, its sources ----
546 // need to be shuffled in strict wqm, but the export itself needs to ----
547 // run in exact mode. ----
548 BBI.Needs |= StateExact; 0
549 if (!(BBI.InNeeds & StateExact)) { 0
550 BBI.InNeeds |= StateExact; 0
551 Worklist.push_back(MBB); 0
552 } ----
553 GlobalFlags |= StateExact; 0
554 III.Disabled = StateWQM | StateStrict; 0
555 } ----
556 continue; 0
557 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::LDS_PARAM_LOAD || 0
558 Opcode == AMDGPU::LDS_DIRECT_LOAD) { ----
559 // Mark these STRICTWQM, but only for the instruction, not its operands. ----
560 // This avoid unnecessarily marking M0 as requiring WQM. ----
561 InstrInfo &II = Instructions[&MI]; 0
562 II.Needs |= StateStrictWQM; 0
563 GlobalFlags |= StateStrictWQM; 0
564 continue; 0
565 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::V_SET_INACTIVE_B32 || 0
566 Opcode == AMDGPU::V_SET_INACTIVE_B64) { ----
567 III.Disabled = StateStrict; 0
568 MachineOperand &Inactive = MI.getOperand(2); 0
569 if (Inactive.isReg()) { 0
570 if (Inactive.isUndef()) { 0
571 LowerToCopyInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
572 } else { ----
573 markOperand(MI, Inactive, StateStrictWWM, Worklist); 0
574 } ----
575 } ----
576 SetInactiveInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
577 continue; 0
578 } else if (TII->isDisableWQM(MI)) { 0
579 BBI.Needs |= StateExact; 0
580 if (!(BBI.InNeeds & StateExact)) { 0
581 BBI.InNeeds |= StateExact; 0
582 Worklist.push_back(MBB); 0
583 } ----
584 GlobalFlags |= StateExact; 0
585 III.Disabled = StateWQM | StateStrict; 0
586 continue; 0
587 } else { ----
588 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::SI_PS_LIVE || Opcode == AMDGPU::SI_LIVE_MASK) { 0
589 LiveMaskQueries.push_back(&MI); 0
590 } else if (Opcode == AMDGPU::SI_KILL_I1_TERMINATOR || 0
591 Opcode == AMDGPU::SI_KILL_F32_COND_IMM_TERMINATOR || 0
592 Opcode == AMDGPU::SI_DEMOTE_I1) { ----
593 KillInstrs.push_back(&MI); 0
594 BBI.NeedsLowering = true; 0
595 } else if (WQMOutputs) { 0
596 // The function is in machine SSA form, which means that physical ----
597 // VGPRs correspond to shader inputs and outputs. Inputs are ----
598 // only used, outputs are only defined. ----
599 // FIXME: is this still valid? ----
600 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.defs()) { 0
601 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
602 continue; 0
603 ----
604 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
605 ----
606 if (!Reg.isVirtual() && 0
607 TRI->hasVectorRegisters(TRI->getPhysRegBaseClass(Reg))) { 0
608 Flags = StateWQM; 0
609 break; 0
610 } ----
611 } ----
612 } ----
613 ----
614 if (!Flags) 0
615 continue; 0
616 } ----
617 ----
618 markInstruction(MI, Flags, Worklist); 0
619 GlobalFlags |= Flags; 0
620 } ----
621 } ----
622 ----
623 // Mark sure that any SET_INACTIVE instructions are computed in WQM if WQM is ----
624 // ever used anywhere in the function. This implements the corresponding ----
625 // semantics of @llvm.amdgcn.set.inactive. ----
626 // Similarly for SOFT_WQM instructions, implementing @llvm.amdgcn.softwqm. ----
627 if (GlobalFlags & StateWQM) { 0
628 for (MachineInstr *MI : SetInactiveInstrs) 0
629 markInstruction(*MI, StateWQM, Worklist); 0
630 for (MachineInstr *MI : SoftWQMInstrs) 0
631 markInstruction(*MI, StateWQM, Worklist); 0
632 } ----
633 ----
634 return GlobalFlags; 0
635 } 0
636 ----
637 void SIWholeQuadMode::propagateInstruction(MachineInstr &MI, 0
638 std::vector& Worklist) { ----
639 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
640 InstrInfo II = Instructions[&MI]; // take a copy to prevent dangling references 0
641 BlockInfo &BI = Blocks[MBB]; 0
642 ----
643 // Control flow-type instructions and stores to temporary memory that are ----
644 // followed by WQM computations must themselves be in WQM. ----
645 if ((II.OutNeeds & StateWQM) && !(II.Disabled & StateWQM) && 0
646 (MI.isTerminator() || (TII->usesVM_CNT(MI) && MI.mayStore()))) { 0
647 Instructions[&MI].Needs = StateWQM; 0
648 II.Needs = StateWQM; 0
649 } ----
650 ----
651 // Propagate to block level ----
652 if (II.Needs & StateWQM) { 0
653 BI.Needs |= StateWQM; 0
654 if (!(BI.InNeeds & StateWQM)) { 0
655 BI.InNeeds |= StateWQM; 0
656 Worklist.push_back(MBB); 0
657 } ----
658 } ----
659 ----
660 // Propagate backwards within block ----
661 if (MachineInstr *PrevMI = MI.getPrevNode()) { 0
662 char InNeeds = (II.Needs & ~StateStrict) | II.OutNeeds; 0
663 if (!PrevMI->isPHI()) { 0
664 InstrInfo &PrevII = Instructions[PrevMI]; 0
665 if ((PrevII.OutNeeds | InNeeds) != PrevII.OutNeeds) { 0
666 PrevII.OutNeeds |= InNeeds; 0
667 Worklist.push_back(PrevMI); 0
668 } ----
669 } ----
670 } ----
671 ----
672 // Propagate WQM flag to instruction inputs ----
673 assert(!(II.Needs & StateExact)); 0
674 ----
675 if (II.Needs != 0) 0
676 markInstructionUses(MI, II.Needs, Worklist); 0
677 ----
678 // Ensure we process a block containing StrictWWM/StrictWQM, even if it does ----
679 // not require any WQM transitions. ----
680 if (II.Needs & StateStrictWWM) 0
681 BI.Needs |= StateStrictWWM; 0
682 if (II.Needs & StateStrictWQM) 0
683 BI.Needs |= StateStrictWQM; 0
684 } 0
685 ----
686 void SIWholeQuadMode::propagateBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
687 std::vector& Worklist) { ----
688 BlockInfo BI = Blocks[&MBB]; // Make a copy to prevent dangling references. 0
689 ----
690 // Propagate through instructions ----
691 if (!MBB.empty()) { 0
692 MachineInstr *LastMI = &*MBB.rbegin(); 0
693 InstrInfo &LastII = Instructions[LastMI]; 0
694 if ((LastII.OutNeeds | BI.OutNeeds) != LastII.OutNeeds) { 0
695 LastII.OutNeeds |= BI.OutNeeds; 0
696 Worklist.push_back(LastMI); 0
697 } ----
698 } ----
699 ----
700 // Predecessor blocks must provide for our WQM/Exact needs. ----
701 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
702 BlockInfo &PredBI = Blocks[Pred]; 0
703 if ((PredBI.OutNeeds | BI.InNeeds) == PredBI.OutNeeds) 0
704 continue; 0
705 ----
706 PredBI.OutNeeds |= BI.InNeeds; 0
707 PredBI.InNeeds |= BI.InNeeds; 0
708 Worklist.push_back(Pred); 0
709 } ----
710 ----
711 // All successors must be prepared to accept the same set of WQM/Exact data. ----
712 for (MachineBasicBlock *Succ : MBB.successors()) { 0
713 BlockInfo &SuccBI = Blocks[Succ]; 0
714 if ((SuccBI.InNeeds | BI.OutNeeds) == SuccBI.InNeeds) 0
715 continue; 0
716 ----
717 SuccBI.InNeeds |= BI.OutNeeds; 0
718 Worklist.push_back(Succ); 0
719 } ----
720 } 0
721 ----
722 char SIWholeQuadMode::analyzeFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
723 std::vector Worklist; 0
724 char GlobalFlags = scanInstructions(MF, Worklist); 0
725 ----
726 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
727 WorkItem WI = Worklist.back(); 0
728 Worklist.pop_back(); 0
729 ----
730 if (WI.MI) 0
731 propagateInstruction(*WI.MI, Worklist); 0
732 else ----
733 propagateBlock(*WI.MBB, Worklist); 0
734 } ----
735 ----
736 return GlobalFlags; 0
737 } 0
738 ----
739 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
740 SIWholeQuadMode::saveSCC(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
741 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Before) { ----
742 Register SaveReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass); 0
743 ----
744 MachineInstr *Save = ----
745 BuildMI(MBB, Before, DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::COPY), SaveReg) 0
746 .addReg(AMDGPU::SCC); 0
747 MachineInstr *Restore = ----
748 BuildMI(MBB, Before, DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::COPY), AMDGPU::SCC) 0
749 .addReg(SaveReg); 0
750 ----
751 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*Save); 0
752 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*Restore); 0
753 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(SaveReg); 0
754 ----
755 return Restore; 0
756 } ----
757 ----
758 MachineBasicBlock *SIWholeQuadMode::splitBlock(MachineBasicBlock *BB, 0
759 MachineInstr *TermMI) { ----
760 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split block " << printMBBReference(*BB) << " @ " 0
761 << *TermMI << "\n"); ----
762 ----
763 MachineBasicBlock *SplitBB = ----
764 BB->splitAt(*TermMI, /*UpdateLiveIns*/ true, LIS); 0
765 ----
766 // Convert last instruction in block to a terminator. ----
767 // Note: this only covers the expected patterns ----
768 unsigned NewOpcode = 0; 0
769 switch (TermMI->getOpcode()) { 0
770 case AMDGPU::S_AND_B32: 0
771 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::S_AND_B32_term; 0
772 break; 0
773 case AMDGPU::S_AND_B64: 0
774 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::S_AND_B64_term; 0
775 break; 0
776 case AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32: 0
777 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32_term; 0
778 break; 0
779 case AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64: 0
780 NewOpcode = AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64_term; 0
781 break; 0
782 default: 0
783 break; 0
784 } ----
785 if (NewOpcode) 0
786 TermMI->setDesc(TII->get(NewOpcode)); 0
787 ----
788 if (SplitBB != BB) { 0
789 // Update dominator trees ----
790 using DomTreeT = DomTreeBase; ----
791 SmallVector DTUpdates; 0
792 for (MachineBasicBlock *Succ : SplitBB->successors()) { 0
793 DTUpdates.push_back({DomTreeT::Insert, SplitBB, Succ}); 0
794 DTUpdates.push_back({DomTreeT::Delete, BB, Succ}); 0
795 } ----
796 DTUpdates.push_back({DomTreeT::Insert, BB, SplitBB}); 0
797 if (MDT) 0
798 MDT->getBase().applyUpdates(DTUpdates); 0
799 if (PDT) 0
800 PDT->getBase().applyUpdates(DTUpdates); 0
801 ----
802 // Link blocks ----
803 MachineInstr *MI = ----
804 BuildMI(*BB, BB->end(), DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::S_BRANCH)) 0
805 .addMBB(SplitBB); 0
806 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*MI); 0
807 } 0
808 ----
809 return SplitBB; 0
810 } ----
811 ----
812 MachineInstr *SIWholeQuadMode::lowerKillF32(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
813 MachineInstr &MI) { ----
814 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
815 unsigned Opcode = 0; 0
816 ----
817 assert(MI.getOperand(0).isReg()); 0
818 ----
819 // Comparison is for live lanes; however here we compute the inverse ----
820 // (killed lanes). This is because VCMP will always generate 0 bits ----
821 // for inactive lanes so a mask of live lanes would not be correct ----
822 // inside control flow. ----
823 // Invert the comparison by swapping the operands and adjusting ----
824 // the comparison codes. ----
825 ----
826 switch (MI.getOperand(2).getImm()) { 0
827 case ISD::SETUEQ: 0
828 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_LG_F32_e64; 0
829 break; 0
830 case ISD::SETUGT: 0
831 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_GE_F32_e64; 0
832 break; 0
833 case ISD::SETUGE: 0
834 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_GT_F32_e64; 0
835 break; 0
836 case ISD::SETULT: 0
837 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_LE_F32_e64; 0
838 break; 0
839 case ISD::SETULE: 0
840 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_LT_F32_e64; 0
841 break; 0
842 case ISD::SETUNE: 0
843 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_EQ_F32_e64; 0
844 break; 0
845 case ISD::SETO: 0
846 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_O_F32_e64; 0
847 break; 0
848 case ISD::SETUO: 0
849 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_U_F32_e64; 0
850 break; 0
851 case ISD::SETOEQ: 0
852 case ISD::SETEQ: ----
853 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_NEQ_F32_e64; 0
854 break; 0
855 case ISD::SETOGT: 0
856 case ISD::SETGT: ----
857 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_NLT_F32_e64; 0
858 break; 0
859 case ISD::SETOGE: 0
860 case ISD::SETGE: ----
861 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_NLE_F32_e64; 0
862 break; 0
863 case ISD::SETOLT: 0
864 case ISD::SETLT: ----
865 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_NGT_F32_e64; 0
866 break; 0
867 case ISD::SETOLE: 0
868 case ISD::SETLE: ----
869 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_NGE_F32_e64; 0
870 break; 0
871 case ISD::SETONE: 0
872 case ISD::SETNE: ----
873 Opcode = AMDGPU::V_CMP_NLG_F32_e64; 0
874 break; 0
875 default: 0
876 llvm_unreachable("invalid ISD:SET cond code"); 0
877 } ----
878 ----
879 // Pick opcode based on comparison type. ----
880 MachineInstr *VcmpMI; ----
881 const MachineOperand &Op0 = MI.getOperand(0); 0
882 const MachineOperand &Op1 = MI.getOperand(1); 0
883 ----
884 // VCC represents lanes killed. ----
885 Register VCC = ST->isWave32() ? AMDGPU::VCC_LO : AMDGPU::VCC; 0
886 ----
887 if (TRI->isVGPR(*MRI, Op0.getReg())) { 0
888 Opcode = AMDGPU::getVOPe32(Opcode); 0
889 VcmpMI = BuildMI(MBB, &MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode)).add(Op1).add(Op0); 0
890 } else { ----
891 VcmpMI = BuildMI(MBB, &MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode)) 0
892 .addReg(VCC, RegState::Define) 0
893 .addImm(0) // src0 modifiers 0
894 .add(Op1) 0
895 .addImm(0) // src1 modifiers 0
896 .add(Op0) 0
897 .addImm(0); // omod 0
898 } ----
899 ----
900 MachineInstr *MaskUpdateMI = ----
901 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AndN2Opc), LiveMaskReg) 0
902 .addReg(LiveMaskReg) 0
903 .addReg(VCC); 0
904 ----
905 // State of SCC represents whether any lanes are live in mask, ----
906 // if SCC is 0 then no lanes will be alive anymore. ----
907 MachineInstr *EarlyTermMI = ----
908 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::SI_EARLY_TERMINATE_SCC0)); 0
909 ----
910 MachineInstr *ExecMaskMI = ----
911 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AndN2Opc), Exec).addReg(Exec).addReg(VCC); 0
912 ----
913 assert(MBB.succ_size() == 1); 0
914 MachineInstr *NewTerm = BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::S_BRANCH)) 0
915 .addMBB(*MBB.succ_begin()); 0
916 ----
917 // Update live intervals ----
918 LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(MI, *VcmpMI); 0
919 MBB.remove(&MI); 0
920 ----
921 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*MaskUpdateMI); 0
922 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*ExecMaskMI); 0
923 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*EarlyTermMI); 0
924 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*NewTerm); 0
925 ----
926 return NewTerm; 0
927 } ----
928 ----
929 MachineInstr *SIWholeQuadMode::lowerKillI1(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
930 MachineInstr &MI, bool IsWQM) { ----
931 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
932 MachineInstr *MaskUpdateMI = nullptr; 0
933 ----
934 const bool IsDemote = IsWQM && (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::SI_DEMOTE_I1); 0
935 const MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(0); 0
936 int64_t KillVal = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
937 MachineInstr *ComputeKilledMaskMI = nullptr; 0
938 Register CndReg = !Op.isImm() ? Op.getReg() : Register(); 0
939 Register TmpReg; 0
940 ----
941 // Is this a static or dynamic kill? ----
942 if (Op.isImm()) { 0
943 if (Op.getImm() == KillVal) { 0
944 // Static: all active lanes are killed ----
945 MaskUpdateMI = BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AndN2Opc), LiveMaskReg) 0
946 .addReg(LiveMaskReg) 0
947 .addReg(Exec); 0
948 } else { ----
949 // Static: kill does nothing ----
950 MachineInstr *NewTerm = nullptr; 0
951 if (MI.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::SI_DEMOTE_I1) { 0
952 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
953 } else { ----
954 assert(MBB.succ_size() == 1); 0
955 NewTerm = BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::S_BRANCH)) 0
956 .addMBB(*MBB.succ_begin()); 0
957 LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(MI, *NewTerm); 0
958 } ----
959 MBB.remove(&MI); 0
960 return NewTerm; 0
961 } ----
962 } else { ----
963 if (!KillVal) { 0
964 // Op represents live lanes after kill, ----
965 // so exec mask needs to be factored in. ----
966 TmpReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(TRI->getBoolRC()); 0
967 ComputeKilledMaskMI = ----
968 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(XorOpc), TmpReg).add(Op).addReg(Exec); 0
969 MaskUpdateMI = BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AndN2Opc), LiveMaskReg) 0
970 .addReg(LiveMaskReg) 0
971 .addReg(TmpReg); 0
972 } else { ----
973 // Op represents lanes to kill ----
974 MaskUpdateMI = BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AndN2Opc), LiveMaskReg) 0
975 .addReg(LiveMaskReg) 0
976 .add(Op); 0
977 } ----
978 } ----
979 ----
980 // State of SCC represents whether any lanes are live in mask, ----
981 // if SCC is 0 then no lanes will be alive anymore. ----
982 MachineInstr *EarlyTermMI = ----
983 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::SI_EARLY_TERMINATE_SCC0)); 0
984 ----
985 // In the case we got this far some lanes are still live, ----
986 // update EXEC to deactivate lanes as appropriate. ----
987 MachineInstr *NewTerm; ----
988 MachineInstr *WQMMaskMI = nullptr; 0
989 Register LiveMaskWQM; 0
990 if (IsDemote) { 0
991 // Demote - deactivate quads with only helper lanes ----
992 LiveMaskWQM = MRI->createVirtualRegister(TRI->getBoolRC()); 0
993 WQMMaskMI = ----
994 BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(WQMOpc), LiveMaskWQM).addReg(LiveMaskReg); 0
995 NewTerm = BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AndOpc), Exec) 0
996 .addReg(Exec) 0
997 .addReg(LiveMaskWQM); 0
998 } else { ----
999 // Kill - deactivate lanes no longer in live mask ----
1000 if (Op.isImm()) { 0
1001 unsigned MovOpc = ST->isWave32() ? AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32 : AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64; 0
1002 NewTerm = BuildMI(MBB, &MI, DL, TII->get(MovOpc), Exec).addImm(0); 0
1003 } else if (!IsWQM) { 0
1004 NewTerm = BuildMI(MBB, &MI, DL, TII->get(AndOpc), Exec) 0
1005 .addReg(Exec) 0
1006 .addReg(LiveMaskReg); 0
1007 } else { ----
1008 unsigned Opcode = KillVal ? AndN2Opc : AndOpc; 0
1009 NewTerm = ----
1010 BuildMI(MBB, &MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode), Exec).addReg(Exec).add(Op); 0
1011 } ----
1012 } ----
1013 ----
1014 // Update live intervals ----
1015 LIS->RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
1016 MBB.remove(&MI); 0
1017 assert(EarlyTermMI); 0
1018 assert(MaskUpdateMI); 0
1019 assert(NewTerm); 0
1020 if (ComputeKilledMaskMI) 0
1021 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*ComputeKilledMaskMI); 0
1022 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*MaskUpdateMI); 0
1023 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*EarlyTermMI); 0
1024 if (WQMMaskMI) 0
1025 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*WQMMaskMI); 0
1026 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*NewTerm); 0
1027 ----
1028 if (CndReg) { 0
1029 LIS->removeInterval(CndReg); 0
1030 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(CndReg); 0
1031 } ----
1032 if (TmpReg) 0
1033 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(TmpReg); 0
1034 if (LiveMaskWQM) 0
1035 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(LiveMaskWQM); 0
1036 ----
1037 return NewTerm; 0
1038 } ----
1039 ----
1040 // Convert a strict mode transition to a pseudo transition. ----
1041 // This still pre-allocates registers to prevent clobbering, ----
1042 // but avoids any EXEC mask changes. ----
1043 void SIWholeQuadMode::lowerPseudoStrictMode(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1044 MachineInstr *Entry, ----
1045 MachineInstr *Exit) { ----
1046 assert(Entry->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::ENTER_STRICT_WQM); 0
1047 assert(Exit->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::EXIT_STRICT_WQM); 0
1048 ----
1049 Register SaveOrig = Entry->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1050 ----
1051 MachineInstr *NewEntry = ----
1052 BuildMI(MBB, Entry, DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::ENTER_PSEUDO_WM)); 0
1053 MachineInstr *NewExit = ----
1054 BuildMI(MBB, Exit, DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::EXIT_PSEUDO_WM)); 0
1055 ----
1056 LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(*Exit, *NewExit); 0
1057 Exit->eraseFromParent(); 0
1058 ----
1059 LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(*Entry, *NewEntry); 0
1060 Entry->eraseFromParent(); 0
1061 ----
1062 LIS->removeInterval(SaveOrig); 0
1063 } 0
1064 ----
1065 // Replace (or supplement) instructions accessing live mask. ----
1066 // This can only happen once all the live mask registers have been created ----
1067 // and the execute state (WQM/StrictWWM/Exact) of instructions is known. ----
1068 void SIWholeQuadMode::lowerBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1069 auto BII = Blocks.find(&MBB); 0
1070 if (BII == Blocks.end()) 0
1071 return; 0
1072 ----
1073 const BlockInfo &BI = BII->second; 0
1074 if (!BI.NeedsLowering) 0
1075 return; 0
1076 ----
1077 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nLowering block " << printMBBReference(MBB) << ":\n"); 0
1078 ----
1079 SmallVector SplitPoints; 0
1080 char State = BI.InitialState; 0
1081 MachineInstr *StrictEntry = nullptr; 0
1082 ----
1083 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range( 0
1084 llvm::make_range(MBB.getFirstNonPHI(), MBB.end()))) { 0
1085 char PreviousState = State; 0
1086 ----
1087 if (StateTransition.count(&MI)) 0
1088 State = StateTransition[&MI]; 0
1089 ----
1090 MachineInstr *SplitPoint = nullptr; 0
1091 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1092 case AMDGPU::SI_DEMOTE_I1: 0
1093 case AMDGPU::SI_KILL_I1_TERMINATOR: ----
1094 SplitPoint = lowerKillI1(MBB, MI, State == StateWQM); 0
1095 break; 0
1096 case AMDGPU::SI_KILL_F32_COND_IMM_TERMINATOR: 0
1097 SplitPoint = lowerKillF32(MBB, MI); 0
1098 break; 0
1099 case AMDGPU::ENTER_STRICT_WQM: 0
1100 StrictEntry = PreviousState == StateWQM ? &MI : nullptr; 0
1101 break; 0
1102 case AMDGPU::EXIT_STRICT_WQM: 0
1103 if (State == StateWQM && StrictEntry) { 0
1104 // Transition WQM -> StrictWQM -> WQM detected. ----
1105 lowerPseudoStrictMode(MBB, StrictEntry, &MI); 0
1106 } ----
1107 StrictEntry = nullptr; 0
1108 break; 0
1109 case AMDGPU::ENTER_STRICT_WWM: 0
1110 case AMDGPU::EXIT_STRICT_WWM: ----
1111 StrictEntry = nullptr; 0
1112 break; 0
1113 default: 0
1114 break; 0
1115 } ----
1116 if (SplitPoint) 0
1117 SplitPoints.push_back(SplitPoint); 0
1118 } ----
1119 ----
1120 // Perform splitting after instruction scan to simplify iteration. ----
1121 if (!SplitPoints.empty()) { 0
1122 MachineBasicBlock *BB = &MBB; 0
1123 for (MachineInstr *MI : SplitPoints) { 0
1124 BB = splitBlock(BB, MI); 0
1125 } ----
1126 } ----
1127 } 0
1128 ----
1129 // Return an iterator in the (inclusive) range [First, Last] at which ----
1130 // instructions can be safely inserted, keeping in mind that some of the ----
1131 // instructions we want to add necessarily clobber SCC. ----
1132 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SIWholeQuadMode::prepareInsertion( 0
1133 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator First, ----
1134 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Last, bool PreferLast, bool SaveSCC) { ----
1135 if (!SaveSCC) 0
1136 return PreferLast ? Last : First; 0
1137 ----
1138 LiveRange &LR = ----
1139 LIS->getRegUnit(*TRI->regunits(MCRegister::from(AMDGPU::SCC)).begin()); 0
1140 auto MBBE = MBB.end(); 0
1141 SlotIndex FirstIdx = First != MBBE ? LIS->getInstructionIndex(*First) 0
1142 : LIS->getMBBEndIdx(&MBB); 0
1143 SlotIndex LastIdx = ----
1144 Last != MBBE ? LIS->getInstructionIndex(*Last) : LIS->getMBBEndIdx(&MBB); 0
1145 SlotIndex Idx = PreferLast ? LastIdx : FirstIdx; 0
1146 const LiveRange::Segment *S; ----
1147 ----
1148 for (;;) { ----
1149 S = LR.getSegmentContaining(Idx); 0
1150 if (!S) 0
1151 break; 0
1152 ----
1153 if (PreferLast) { 0
1154 SlotIndex Next = S->start.getBaseIndex(); 0
1155 if (Next < FirstIdx) 0
1156 break; 0
1157 Idx = Next; 0
1158 } else { ----
1159 MachineInstr *EndMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(S->end.getBaseIndex()); 0
1160 assert(EndMI && "Segment does not end on valid instruction"); 0
1161 auto NextI = std::next(EndMI->getIterator()); 0
1162 if (NextI == MBB.end()) 0
1163 break; 0
1164 SlotIndex Next = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*NextI); 0
1165 if (Next > LastIdx) 0
1166 break; 0
1167 Idx = Next; 0
1168 } ----
1169 } 0
1170 ----
1171 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI; 0
1172 ----
1173 if (MachineInstr *MI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(Idx)) 0
1174 MBBI = MI; 0
1175 else { ----
1176 assert(Idx == LIS->getMBBEndIdx(&MBB)); 0
1177 MBBI = MBB.end(); 0
1178 } ----
1179 ----
1180 // Move insertion point past any operations modifying EXEC. ----
1181 // This assumes that the value of SCC defined by any of these operations ----
1182 // does not need to be preserved. ----
1183 while (MBBI != Last) { 0
1184 bool IsExecDef = false; 0
1185 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MBBI->all_defs()) { 0
1186 IsExecDef |= 0
1187 MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::EXEC_LO || MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::EXEC; 0
1188 } ----
1189 if (!IsExecDef) 0
1190 break; 0
1191 MBBI++; 0
1192 S = nullptr; 0
1193 } ----
1194 ----
1195 if (S) 0
1196 MBBI = saveSCC(MBB, MBBI); 0
1197 ----
1198 return MBBI; 0
1199 } ----
1200 ----
1201 void SIWholeQuadMode::toExact(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
1202 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Before, ----
1203 Register SaveWQM) { ----
1204 bool IsTerminator = Before == MBB.end(); 0
1205 if (!IsTerminator) { 0
1206 auto FirstTerm = MBB.getFirstTerminator(); 0
1207 if (FirstTerm != MBB.end()) { 0

1296 void SIWholeQuadMode::processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, bool IsEntry) { 0

1301 BlockInfo &BI = BII->second; 0

1303 // This is a non-entry block that is WQM throughout, so no need to do ----
1304 // anything. ----

1323 if (II != IE && II->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::COPY) 0

1325 } ----

1330 ----
1331 // This stores the first instruction where it's safe to switch from Strict ----

1333 // as, or after, FirstWQM since if it's safe to switch to/from Strict, it must ----

1338 BI.InitialState = State; 0

1340 for (;;) { ----

1343 char OutNeeds = 0; 0
1344 ----
1345 if (FirstWQM == IE) 0
1346 FirstWQM = II; 0
1347 ----
1348 if (FirstStrict == IE) 0
1349 FirstStrict = II; 0
1350 ----
1351 // First, figure out the allowed states (Needs) based on the propagated ----
1352 // flags. ----
1353 if (II != IE) { 0

1356 if (MI.isTerminator() || TII->mayReadEXEC(*MRI, MI)) { 0

1358 if (III != Instructions.end()) { 0

1361 else if (III->second.Needs & StateStrictWQM) 0

1368 } ----
1369 } else { ----
1370 // If the instruction doesn't actually need a correct EXEC, then we can ----
1371 // safely leave Strict mode enabled. ----
1372 Needs = StateExact | StateWQM | StateStrict; 0
1373 } ----
1374 ----
1375 // Exact mode exit can occur in terminators, but must be before branches. ----
1376 if (MI.isBranch() && OutNeeds == StateExact) 0
1377 Needs = StateExact; 0
1378 ----
1379 ++Next; 0
1380 } else { ----
1381 // End of basic block ----
1382 if (BI.OutNeeds & StateWQM) 0
1383 Needs = StateWQM; 0
1384 else if (BI.OutNeeds == StateExact) 0
1385 Needs = StateExact; 0
1386 else ----
1387 Needs = StateWQM | StateExact; 0
1388 } ----
1389 ----
1390 // Now, transition if necessary. ----
1391 if (!(Needs & State)) { 0
1392 MachineBasicBlock::iterator First; 0
1393 if (State == StateStrictWWM || Needs == StateStrictWWM || 0
1394 State == StateStrictWQM || Needs == StateStrictWQM) { 0
1395 // We must switch to or from Strict mode. ----
1396 First = FirstStrict; 0
1397 } else { ----
1398 // We only need to switch to/from WQM, so we can use FirstWQM. ----
1399 First = FirstWQM; 0
1400 } ----
1401 ----
1402 // Whether we need to save SCC depends on start and end states. ----
1403 bool SaveSCC = false; 0
1404 switch (State) { 0
1405 case StateExact: 0
1406 case StateStrictWWM: ----
1407 case StateStrictWQM: ----
1408 // Exact/Strict -> Strict: save SCC ----
1409 // Exact/Strict -> WQM: save SCC if WQM mask is generated from exec ----
1410 // Exact/Strict -> Exact: no save ----
1411 SaveSCC = (Needs & StateStrict) || ((Needs & StateWQM) && WQMFromExec); 0
1412 break; 0
1413 case StateWQM: 0
1414 // WQM -> Exact/Strict: save SCC ----
1415 SaveSCC = !(Needs & StateWQM); 0
1416 break; 0
1417 default: 0
1418 llvm_unreachable("Unknown state"); 0
1419 break; ----
1420 } ----
1421 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Before = ----
1422 prepareInsertion(MBB, First, II, Needs == StateWQM, SaveSCC); 0
1423 ----
1424 if (State & StateStrict) { 0
1425 assert(State == StateStrictWWM || State == StateStrictWQM); 0
1426 assert(SavedNonStrictReg); 0
1427 fromStrictMode(MBB, Before, SavedNonStrictReg, NonStrictState, State); 0
1428 ----
1429 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(SavedNonStrictReg); 0
1430 SavedNonStrictReg = 0; 0
1431 State = NonStrictState; 0
1432 } ----
1433 ----
1434 if (Needs & StateStrict) { 0
1435 NonStrictState = State; 0
1436 assert(Needs == StateStrictWWM || Needs == StateStrictWQM); 0
1437 assert(!SavedNonStrictReg); 0
1438 SavedNonStrictReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(BoolRC); 0
1439 ----
1440 toStrictMode(MBB, Before, SavedNonStrictReg, Needs); 0
1441 State = Needs; 0
1442 ----
1443 } else { ----
1444 if (State == StateWQM && (Needs & StateExact) && !(Needs & StateWQM)) { 0
1445 if (!WQMFromExec && (OutNeeds & StateWQM)) { 0
1446 assert(!SavedWQMReg); 0
1447 SavedWQMReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(BoolRC); 0

1449 ----

1451 State = StateExact; 0
1452 } else if (State == StateExact && (Needs & StateWQM) && 0

1454 assert(WQMFromExec == (SavedWQMReg == 0)); 0
1455 ----

1457 ----
1458 if (SavedWQMReg) { 0
1459 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(SavedWQMReg); 0
1460 SavedWQMReg = 0; 0
1461 } ----
1462 State = StateWQM; 0
1463 } else { ----
1464 // We can get here if we transitioned from StrictWWM to a ----
1465 // non-StrictWWM state that already matches our needs, but we ----
1466 // shouldn't need to do anything. ----
1467 assert(Needs & State); 0
1468 } ----
1469 } ----
1470 } ----
1471 ----
1472 if (Needs != (StateExact | StateWQM | StateStrict)) { 0
1473 if (Needs != (StateExact | StateWQM)) 0
1474 FirstWQM = IE; 0

1476 } ----
1477 ----
1478 if (II == IE) 0

1480 ----
1481 II = Next; 0
1482 } 0
1483 assert(!SavedWQMReg); 0

1501 void SIWholeQuadMode::lowerCopyInstrs() { 0
1502 for (MachineInstr *MI : LowerToMovInstrs) { 0
1503 assert(MI->getNumExplicitOperands() == 2); 0
1504 ----
1505 const Register Reg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1506 ----
1507 const TargetRegisterClass *regClass = ----
1508 TRI->getRegClassForOperandReg(*MRI, MI->getOperand(0)); 0
1509 if (TRI->isVGPRClass(regClass)) { 0

1513 // Check that it already implicitly depends on exec (like all VALU movs ----
1514 // should do). ----
1515 assert(any_of(MI->implicit_operands(), [](const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
1516 return MO.isUse() && MO.getReg() == AMDGPU::EXEC; ----
1517 })); ----
1518 } else { ----
1519 // Remove early-clobber and exec dependency from simple SGPR copies. ----
1520 // This allows some to be eliminated during/post RA. ----
1521 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "simplify SGPR copy: " << *MI); 0
1522 if (MI->getOperand(0).isEarlyClobber()) { 0
1523 LIS->removeInterval(Reg); 0
1524 MI->getOperand(0).setIsEarlyClobber(false); 0
1525 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(Reg); 0
1526 } ----

1528 while (Index >= 0) { 0
1529 MI->removeOperand(Index); 0
1530 Index = MI->findRegisterUseOperandIdx(AMDGPU::EXEC); 0
1531 } ----
1532 MI->setDesc(TII->get(AMDGPU::COPY)); 0
1533 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " -> " << *MI); 0
1534 } ----
1535 } ----
1536 for (MachineInstr *MI : LowerToCopyInstrs) { 0
1537 if (MI->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_SET_INACTIVE_B32 || 0
1538 MI->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_SET_INACTIVE_B64) { 0
1539 assert(MI->getNumExplicitOperands() == 3); 0
1540 // the only reason we should be here is V_SET_INACTIVE has ----
1541 // an undef input so it is being replaced by a simple copy. ----
1542 // There should be a second undef source that we should remove. ----
1543 assert(MI->getOperand(2).isUndef()); 0
1544 MI->removeOperand(2); 0
1545 MI->untieRegOperand(1); 0
1546 } else { ----
1547 assert(MI->getNumExplicitOperands() == 2); 0
1548 } ----
1549 ----
1550 unsigned CopyOp = MI->getOperand(1).isReg() 0
1551 ? (unsigned)AMDGPU::COPY 0
1552 : TII->getMovOpcode(TRI->getRegClassForOperandReg( 0
1553 *MRI, MI->getOperand(0))); 0

1578 bool SIWholeQuadMode::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0

1580 << " ------------- \n"); ----

1584 Blocks.clear(); 0

1587 LowerToMovInstrs.clear(); 0

1606 AndSaveExecTermOpc = AMDGPU::S_AND_SAVEEXEC_B32_term; 0
1607 WQMOpc = AMDGPU::S_WQM_B32; 0
1608 Exec = AMDGPU::EXEC_LO; 0
1609 } else { ----
1610 AndOpc = AMDGPU::S_AND_B64; 0
1611 AndTermOpc = AMDGPU::S_AND_B64_term; 0
1612 AndN2Opc = AMDGPU::S_ANDN2_B64; 0

1616 WQMOpc = AMDGPU::S_WQM_B64; 0
1617 Exec = AMDGPU::EXEC; 0
1618 } ----
1619 ----
1620 const char GlobalFlags = analyzeFunction(MF); 0
1621 const bool NeedsLiveMask = !(KillInstrs.empty() && LiveMaskQueries.empty()); 0
1622 ----
1623 LiveMaskReg = Exec; 0
1624 ----
1625 // Shader is simple does not need any state changes or any complex lowering ----
1626 if (!(GlobalFlags & (StateWQM | StateStrict)) && LowerToCopyInstrs.empty() && 0
1627 LowerToMovInstrs.empty() && KillInstrs.empty()) { 0

1643 ----
1644 LLVM_DEBUG(printInfo()); 0
1645 ----

1647 lowerCopyInstrs(); 0
1648 ----
1649 // Shader only needs WQM ----
1650 if (GlobalFlags == StateWQM) { 0

1652 .addReg(Exec); 0
1653 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*MI); 0
1654 lowerKillInstrs(true); 0
1655 } else { ----
1656 for (auto BII : Blocks) 0
1657 processBlock(*BII.first, BII.first == &Entry); 0
1658 // Lowering blocks causes block splitting so perform as a second pass. ----
1659 for (auto BII : Blocks) 0
1660 lowerBlock(*BII.first); 0
1661 } ----
1662 ----
1663 // Compute live range for live mask ----
1664 if (LiveMaskReg != Exec) 0
1665 LIS->createAndComputeVirtRegInterval(LiveMaskReg); 0
1666 ----
1667 // Physical registers like SCC aren't tracked by default anyway, so just ----
1668 // removing the ranges we computed is the simplest option for maintaining ----
1669 // the analysis results. ----
1670 LIS->removeAllRegUnitsForPhysReg(AMDGPU::SCC); 0
1671 ----
1672 // If we performed any kills then recompute EXEC ----
1673 if (!KillInstrs.empty()) 0

1677 } ----
